Install and setup MySQL - <https://github.com/sid7590/AWS/blob/master/MySQL>
Connect MySQL with wordpress installation - same as above

Make the required changes in the siteName.conf file. It is located in /etc/apache2/sites-available
Run the below command from within the directory /etc/apache2/sites-enabled
a2ensite siteName.conf
systemctl reload apache2
A new file with the sitrName.conf should be available within the /etc/apache2/sites-enabled director
